<HEADLINE> International Fair on Agro-Technologies Opens in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Qingdao International
Fair on Agricultural Sciences and Technologies opened in Pingdu
city, east China's Shandong Province, today.
</P>
<P>
The fair is jointly sponsored by the State Science and
Technology Commission, the Qingdao city government, and some
state ministries.
</P>
<P>
Visitors will have the opportunity to exchange ideas on new
agro-techniques, see a variety of new means of agricultural
production and agro-products, and view an exhibition of new
achievements in the field of farm produce processing.
</P>
<P>
Awards will be given to participants who have made
contributions to the invention or popularization of new
technology and products.
</P>
<P>
Among those attending the fair are corporations from 14
countries and regions and units from 27 provinces and regions
across the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
