<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Record Number of UK TV Audience Watch Diana Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A record 31.5 million British
TV audience watched the funeral service of Diana, the Princess of
Wales, last Saturday, making it the biggest UK television event in
history.
</P>
<P>
Initial figures provided by the British Audience Research
Bureau showed that 59 percent of the country's population were
watching the service at the peak time. Millions more were
listening on radio in cars and at work.
</P>
<P>
The figures, which represent three quarters of the country's
adult population, exceeded the estimated 22 million who watched
the wedding in 1981 of Diana and Prince Charles, and the 19
million who watched Sir Winston Churchill's funeral in 1965.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that previously the highest television audience
was 26.2 million for the England v. Germany Euro 96 semi-final
last year.
</P>
<P>
Television executives said that it was "almost impossible" to
assess how many had watched around the world. The procession and
the funeral service were also broadcast to 187 other countries by
the British Broadcasting Corporation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
