<HEADLINE> CPC's Foreign Exchanges Making Notable Progress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Communist Party of China
(CPC) has been making "new and important" achievements in its
exchanges with foreign parties since 1992, the year of the CPC's
14th congress.
</P>
<P>
The claim was made by Dai Bingguo, head of the International
Department under the CPC Central Committee, in a speech today
aired on the Beijing-based China Radio International.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, CPC has made a lot of political
friends of many types and in various ways, according to the Party
official.
</P>
<P>
This has been scored under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's
thinking on diplomacy, the leadship of the CPC Central Committee
with Jiang Zemin at the core, and the principle of "creating a
favorable international environment for China's economic growth,
and reform and opening-up program," Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
By adapting to the new situation after the Cold War and seizing
opportunities, the CPC has made new progress in foreign exchanges
over the years, Dai said.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the drastic changes in East Europe, the break-up of
the former Soviet Union, the changes of ruling parties and the
emergence of new parties in this region afterwards, Dai said, the
CPC has been steadfastly pursuing the principle of
non-interference in the internal affairs of other parties.
</P>
<P>
China respects these countries' choices of individual paths of
development, and has tried to cooperate with parties in these
countries on the basis of seeking common ground while reserving
differences, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC's Foreign Exchanges Making Notable Progress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Different types and degrees of contact have been established
between the CPC and various political organizations in these
countries, Dai noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the CPC has forged ties with 50 major political parties
in 36 African countries, who are in power, or participating in
government or out of office.
</P>
<P>
The CPC set up and advanced ties with almost all the Japanese
parties promptly when many political bodies emerged after profound
changes in Japan's political structure in 1993, he continued.
</P>
<P>
The CPC has also befriended parties who have different
political attitudes and philosophies, Dai stressed.
</P>
<P>
While developing friendship with communist and labor parties
with same or similar political orientation, the CPC has increased
exchanges with other legal parties and political organizations of
various types, according to Dai.
</P>
<P>
Dai attributed the improvement of party-to-party relations
between China and neighboring countries to the overall growth of
bilateral ties and mutual understanding and trust.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, the CPC has also been conducting
friendly cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual respect
and benefit with some right-wing, conservative and socialist
parties in developed countries, although they terminated or put a
freeze on exchanges with the CPC out of ideological reasons after
1989, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the CPC has made unremitting efforts to promote the
friendly cooperation between nations and safeguard national
sovereignty, Dai added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC's Foreign Exchanges Making Notable Progress (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The CPC has contributed a lot to the enhancement of mutual
understanding and friendship between China and other countries,"
Dai said.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, he noted, the CPC has helped step up
China's work to improve foreign relations by seeking support from
the ruling parties of developing nations in Asia, Africa and Latin
America on issues related to China's sovereignty, such as the
issues of human rights, Taiwan and Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Dai also stressed the important role of the CPC's exchanges
with major parties, either in or out of office, in maintaining
stable bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the contributions the CPC has made in developing
the party-to-party relations with countries that do not have
diplomatic ties with China.
</P>
<P>
For instance, Dai said, the CPC has links with over 20 parties
of most of the 15 Latin American countries that have not forged
diplomatic ties with China, and it has made friends with many
noted figures in these countries.
</P>
<P>
Dai said the CPC has attached great importance to economic
factors in its foreign relations, and helped promote China's
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
He said the CPC has intensified the study and researches on
economic experiences in foreign countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC's Foreign Exchanges Making Notable Progress (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The CPC has conducted field studies and seminars on
policy-making in such areas as sustainable agricultural growth,
reform in large and medium-sized enterprises, inflation control,
foreign investment, social security, environmental protection,
professional training and employment, according to Dai.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, China has achieved social stability
and economic growth, strengthened the overall national power, and
elevated the country's international status, he said.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, he noted, the CPC has gained increasingly
higher prestige, and its strategies and experiences in handling
party and state affairs have drawn growing interest from foreign
parties.
</P>
<P>
Dai said the CPC Central Committee has attached much importance
to the Party's foreign affairs. Direct talks between leaders of
the CPC and foreign parties have strongly promoted CPC's
international image and helped foreign parties better understand
the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Finally, Dai noted, the CPC, at the turn of the century, will
strive to make the most of the advantages in its foreign
relationships, and to advance cooperation with foreign parties.
</P>
<P>
The CPC will make new contributions to the friendship and
mutually-beneficial ties between nations, and the everlasting
peace, stability and development of the world and the humanity,
Dai said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
