<HEADLINE> Several Hundred Dead in Haiti Ferry Sinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A ferry sank off Haiti's
west coast today and several hundred people on board were feared
dead, Haiti's Radio Metropole said.
</P>
<P>
The packed ferry carrying about 800 people sank on its way to
the island of La Gonave from the northwestern port of Montrouis,
the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The radio put the death toll at between 300 to 400. It said
that 25 bodies have been recovered and about 60 survivors have
been rescued. 
</P>
</TEXT>
