<TEXT>
<P>
The packed ferry carrying about 800 people sank on its way to
the island of La Gonave from the northwestern port of Montrouis,
the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The radio put the death toll at between 300 to 400. It said
that 25 bodies have been recovered and about 60 survivors have
been rescued. (Haiti-Ferry)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- A French court Monday suspended a three-month jail
sentence and levied a 50,000-franc (about 8,300 U.S. dollars) fine
in a verdict against Catherine Megret, the mayor of the
southwestern city of Vitrolles.
</P>
<P>
The Correctional Tribunal of Aix-en-Provence condemned Megret
for making racist statements taunting immigrants and suggesting
racial inequality in a February interview with the German daily
Berliner Zeitung (Berlin Daily). (France-National Front-Mayor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOGADISHU -- Three people were killed and four others were
wounded when armed militiamen among the supporters of Hussein
Mohamed Aidid exchanged heavy fire at Afgoe road near the Somali
capital Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses said, the shooting began when a convoy of vehicles
transporting khat were refused access to reach the capital
Mogadishu by militiamen at a check point near the strategic K-7
junction. (Somalia-Clash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- Environment ministers from central and East
European countries held an informal talk with their counterparts
from the European Union (EU) Monday to discuss pre-accession
preparation on environment issues.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on the implementation of EU environmental
legislation in the central and East European countries, which is a
part of an environmental approximation program.
(Europe-Environment-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI-- Indian Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral said
Monday that India would prefer its nuclear option open to meet
unforeseen circumstances.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the two-day international seminar on the role of
nuclear energy for sustainable development here, he said that
India has proved time and again that even when it has capability
to make nuclear weapons, it would not do so. (India-PM-Nuclear
Option)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- China values its relationship with Australia, and
advancement of bilateral ties in politics, economy, science and
technology is the common goal and in the best interests of the two
peoples, Premier Li Peng said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting Monday afternoon with Australian Deputy Prime
Minister and Minister of Trade Tim Fischer, Li extended a welcome
to Fischer who is visiting China for the second time since
assuming office.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 25th anniversary of the establishment of
diplomatic ties between China and Australia. (China-Li
Peng-Australia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The main computer system on Russia's Mir space
station broke down, resulting in a shutdown of all systems except
life-support functions, a Russian space official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The computer shut itself off for unknown reasons, said Valery
Lyndin, spokesman for Russia's Mission Control.
</P>
<P>
The crew on board, two Russian cosmonauts and one American
astronaut, were not in any immediate danger, the Associated Press
quoted Lyndin as saying. (Russia-Mir-Computer Breakdown) 
</P>
