<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women's Head Highlights Gender Equality at SADC </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BLANTYRE (MALAWI), September 8 (Xinhua) -- Gertrude Mongella,
chairperson of the U.N. Fourth World Conference on Women, today
highly praised Southern African Development Community (SADC) for
taking gender equality into its action plan.
</P>
<P>
Mongella, who presided over the women's conference in Beijing
in 1995, said here today that it is an important "milestone"
towards democracy and development for SADC to integrate gender
into its program of action.
</P>
<P>
Mongella, who is invited to the SADC summit by its Chairman
Nelson Mandela as an honored guest, said at the opening of the
summit that gender equality is an inalienable right and
pre-requisite for real development and true democracy.
</P>
<P>
The women's leader quoted a song by an African woman that "I
am not asking money although I am in need of it... I have only
one request: that the roadblocks be removed from my way."
</P>
<P>
The full empowerment of women in the region, Mongella said, is
what women here are demanding.
</P>
<P>
Gender equality, a basic human right which makes economic
development work, is the key to the progress of SADC, she said.
</P>
<P>
The SADC ministerial council has approved last week the
Regional Plan of Action on Gender to ensure equality between men
and women in the sharing of power and decision making at all
levels, Mongella said.
</P>
<P>
Adequate promotion and protection of the human rights of women
and children is also covered in the plan.
</P>
<P>
Mongella also called for sufficient resources to make a
"meaningful difference", as too often, similar institutions have
been marginalized, under-resourced and used as "dumping grounds
for gender issues.
</P>
<P>
SADC, a 12-member group officially launched in August 1992, is
aimed at promoting economic integration towards a fully developed
common market.
</P>
<P>
Protocals on gener equality, mining, education, ban on the
production, use and stockpiling of anti-personnel landmines in
the region is to be passed on the one-day SADC summit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
