<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Several Hundred Dead in Haiti Ferry Sinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A ferry sank off Haiti's
west coast today and several hundred people on board were feared
dead, Haiti's Radio Metropole said.
</P>
<P>
The ferry "La Belle Gonaidienne" carrying about 800 people sank
in the gulf of Gonave on its way to the island of La Gonave from
the northwestern port of Montrouis, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The radio put the death toll at between 300 to 400. It said
that 25 bodies have been recovered and about 60 survivors have
been rescued.
</P>
<P>
Policemen from the nearby St. Marc police station were
assisting a rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Coast Guard in Miami has sent a helicopter, vessels and
medical supplies to the site of the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
