<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Large-scale Electronics Fair Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) will stage its first large-scale
international electronics fair next month, with participation of
over 1,100 exhibitors from 19 countries and regions, the Trade
Development Council said today.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release circulated here, the participants
will occupy over 1,600 booths and an exhibition area of more than
33,000 square meters. This represents an increase of 15 percent
over the number of exhibitors in 1996, it added.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the council, the Hong Kong Electronics Fair 1997
will be held from October 14 to 17 at the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center Extension, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Multimedia will be one of the highlights of the fair with a
wide array of innovative products being displayed under one roof.
Other exhibits include home entertainment and telecom products,
consumer electronics and gadgets, audio visual and home appliances
as well as security systems.
</P>
<P>
The council's assistant executive director C.S. Lee was quoted
as saying that "it will be a prime occasion for electronics
companies to acquire the latest market information of the
industry, and provide buyers with a one-stop-shop for souring."
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong has become an electronics souring center in Asia
because of its manufacturing strength and comprehensive trade
network," Lee said, adding that "the accomplishment is
demonstrated by our exports performance."
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Hong Kong's total exports of electronics grew by three
 percent to 390 billion Hong Kong dollars. In the first six months
 of this year, the figure was 188 billion Hong Kong dollars, up
six percent compared with the same period of last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
