<HEADLINE> China Rejuvenated by Reform, Opening-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Athens, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Some Greek figures said that
the reform and opening-up policy has rejuvenated China and the
forthcoming 15th Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
will decide the future course for China.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, President of Aegean
Television Station Peter Papaconstantinou said that because China
stuck to the right direction in the past decade, the once poor and
old civilized country is at last rejuvenated and witnessing great
developments and changes.
</P>
<P>
"A more prosperous and more powerful China serves as the
foundation for development of Asia and the world as a whole," said
Papaconstantinou, who is also the managing director of the
newspaper Morning News.
</P>
<P>
"Stability and peace in the Asian region will, in a large
degree, lie in on the stability of China," he said.
</P>
<P>
He wished the CPC's 15th congress a success.
</P>
<P>
The congress is drawing the attention of the world because it
will set a future course for China, whose future development and
that of the world is inter-related, he said.
</P>
<P>
Deputy President of the Greek-Chinese Friendship Association
Georgios G. Tsakonas said that thanks to Deng Xiaoping's
opening-up policy, there has been unprecedented progress in the
Chinese economy and the 1.2 billion Chinese people have embarked
on the road to better lives.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China has a growing economy with a great
potential market, which is not only good for China but also
conducive to the development of the world economy.
</P>
<P>
Stavros Nikolakopoulos, chairman of Greece's Euro-Chinese
Center for Research and Development, has visited China 14
times.
</P>
<P>
He said that he has followed the entire process of China's
opening-up to the outside world, which has not only resulted in
China's unprecedented economic growth for more than a decade, but
also laid the foundation for China to become the world's leading
economic power.
</P>
<P>
For the world and China, Deng Xiaoping was a great man with
extraordinary vision, he said. The policy he initiated opened the
gate to prosperity and power for China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
