<HEADLINE> Fourteen-Nation Joint Military Exercise Starts in Latvia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The joint military exercise
code named Cooperative Best Effort-97 started today in Adaz'i of
Latvia, involving 300 soldiers from 14 NATO and non-NATO
countries, Russia's Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Taking part in the exercise are the United States, Canada,
Norway, the Netherlands, Latvia, Estonia, Finland, Poland,
Hungary,Lithunia, Moldova, Sweden, Ukraine and Macedonia.
