<HEADLINE> First Chinese Pencil Factory Goes Into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The first pencil factory built
with Chinese investment in Germany went into operation today in
the northeast German town of Neustadt-Glewe.
</P>
<P>
The North-German Pencil Factory, a subsidiary of the First
Pencil Co. Ltd. from Shanghai, was built with 2.5 million German
marks (1.4 million U.S. dollars) of investment from the Chinese
side and has a planned annual output of 100 million pencils.
</P>
<P>
With the relatively cheap raw materials from China and lacquer
coating from Germany, Chinese investors hope that the pencils will
have a good sale in Europe as well as in the United States and
South America.
</P>
<P>
The First Pencil Co. Ltd. of Shanghai is the largest Chinese
pencil manufacturer which already boasts a big share in the Asian
market. Its new subsidiary in Neustadt-Glewe is also the first
ever production plant set up by Chinese investors in Germany.
</P>
</TEXT>
