The ferry La Belle Gonaivienne sank at dawn near Montrouis,
about 50 miles northwest of the capital, before leaving the port
of Anse-a-Galets on Gonave Island in Port-au-Prince Bay.
</P>
<P>
Radio Metropole and Haiti-Inter reported that 25 bodies washed
ashore.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was unknown. 
