<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Chief Report on Peacekeeping, Peace-building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Maintaining and
restoring international peace and security was a fundamental
purpose of the United Nations, said Secretary-General Kofi Annan
in his report published today.
</P>
<P>
Annan said that currently, approximately 22,500 soldiers and
civilian police were serving in 16 missions in countries around
the world. All help stablize potentially volatile situations, and
many involved extensive cooperation between the United States and
the regional organizations.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief said in the Balkans, the United Nations Mission in
Bosnia and Herzegovina and its International Police Task Force
worked closely with the NATO Stabilization Force to convert into
reality the undertakings made at Dayton, Ohio. The United Nations
Transitional Administration for Eastern Slavonia achieved
significant aims with the demilitarization of the local Serb
forces, and in facilitating the elections held in April 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that the United Nations Preventive Deployment Force was
achieving its mandate in the former Yugoslav Republic of
Macedonia, and the United Nations Mission of Observers in Prevlaka
continued to monitor the situation in that area.
</P>
<P>
In Georgia, he said, the United Nations Observer Mission
cooperated with Commonwealth of Independent States peacekeeping
forces to enable parties to seek a political solution. It
supported the negotiation process that resulted in the general
peace agreement signed in Moscow in June 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said in Haiti, the United Nations was assisting in the
rebuilding if that country's police force, and working with the
Organization of American States in the field of human rights.
</P>
<P>
The chief said the United Nations Observer Mission in Liberia
was nearing the completion of its mandate, which had pursued in
conjunction with the economic Community of West African States, to
monitor a ceasefire and verify disarmament and demobilization.
Those steps paved the way for the elections and installation of a
new government in the summer of 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said so many post-cold-war conflicts had taken the form of
internal factional violence and civil strife that had significant
external repercussions.
</P>
<P>
He stressed peacekeeping in the sense of avoid a relapse into
armed conflict is a necessary but not sufficient condition for
establishing the foundations of an enduring and just peace.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out areas of UN peacekeeping activity should include
military security, civil law and order, human rights,refugees and
displaced persons, elections, local administration, involvement in
public utilities, health, education, finance, reconstruction and
general attempts to return society to some sense of normality.
</P>
</TEXT>
