<HEADLINE> Porsche Posts Record Profits in 1996-97 Business Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- German sports car manufacturer
Porsche today reported record profits of 96.2 million marks (53.4
million U.S. dollars) in the 1996-97 business year ending July 31,
which doubled the figure in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The result came on group revenues of four billion marks (2.2
billion dollars), an increase of 43 percent over the year before.
</P>
<P>
Production in the 1996-97 business year grew by 60 percent to
32,300 cars, with about half of the cars being the new two-seater
Boxster.
</P>
<P>
Porsche said that its sales increased by 68 percent to 32,300
cars, noting that only one-third of the cars were sold in home
market.
</P>
<P>
The company expected its revenues in the 1997-98 business year
to rise by 13 percent to 4.5 billion marks and sales to rise by 18
percent to 38,000 cars.  
</P>
