<HEADLINE> Chinese PC Maker Enters Asia-Pacific Top Ten </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese personal computer
maker recently was named one of the top ten sellers in the
Asia-Pacific region in a survey on the region's PC market
conducted by Dataquest, a famous market surveyor.
</P>
<P>
The survey also shows that China has become the biggest PC
consumer in the region, taking up 23 percent of the total regional
sales, with Japan excluded.
</P>
<P>
Legend Computer, which ranked first in Chinese market sales,
was elevated from 13th to eighth place, the survey report
says. And it is the first Chinese PC vendor to enter the top ten
list.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that Legend's market share in the Asia-Pacific
region in the first half of 1997 rose to 2.45 percent from 1.83
percent in 1996. Its 33.88 percent of increase beat other top ten
PC vendors.
</P>
<P>
The Legend computer remain the best seller the in home market
in the first half of this year, according to Dataquest.
</P>
<P>
Taking eighth place in Asia-Pacific PC sales is merely the
first step in Legend's development strategy, a spokesman of Legend
said.
</P>
<P>
Legend aims to enter the top five list of Asia-Pacific PC sales
while maintaining its leading status in the domestic market by the
year 2000, the spokesman said, adding that the annual PC
production and sales of the company is expected to reach one
million units by that time.
</P>
<P>
The market share of an Asia-Pacific top five PC seller is
estimated at five percent, the spokesman pointed out, and there is
still a big gap between that number and Legend's current standing.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the Chinese PC market recorded a rise of 39.1 percent,
in spite of a slowing global increase which is reflected in the
20.19 and 15.53 percent growth in the Asia-Pacific region and the world
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Up four percentage points over the beginning of the year,
Legend currently occupies 12.06 percent of the Chinese market,
almost twice the percentage of the second largest seller in
China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
