<HEADLINE> Fireworks Display to Be Staged in HK on National Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The first post-return
fireworks display will be held on October 1 to mark the 48th
anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China,
according to a press release circulated here tonight.
</P>
<P>
The fireworks display is expected to begin at 21:45 on October
1 and is scheduled to last for 23 minutes over Victoria Harbor.
Featuring 19,000 fireworks shells, the display will be launched
from four barges, anchored in three locations in the harbor.
</P>
<P>
The event is sponsored by the Association of Hong Kong
Guangdong Community Organizations for Celebration of the Return of
Hong Kong to China Limited, and will be co-organized by the
Provisional Urban Council.
</P>
<P>
With a sponsorship of 3.8 million Hong Kong dollars (some half
a million U.S. dollars), the fireworks shells will be sourced from
provinces across China. 
</P>
