<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0089 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Records Stable Industrial Growth in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's industrial enterprises
above township-level generated an added value of 162.1 billion
yuan last month, an increase of 10.9 percent over the
same period of 1996, said a report released by the State Statistics
Bureau (SSB) today.
</P>
<P>
All the country's state-run enterprises registered an added
value of 93 billion yuan in August, up 8.4 percent over the
corresponding period of last year, statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Especially, the growth rate of the state-owned sector stood at 5.9
percent, which was 0.6 percentage points higher than the average
for the January-July period, the SSB report said.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the slowdown trend continued in China's
collectively-owned sector, of which the growth rate dropped to 8.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Other economic sectors grew at a rate of 16.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to the SSB sources, in August the sales rate for
industrial products exceeded the average in the first seven months
this year and hit 96.7 percent, up 0.2 percentage points over the
same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The country's energy output in August climbed to 104 million
tons of standard coal, up 3.2 percent compared with that in August
of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the output of major raw materials, including
pig iron, steel and non-ferrous metals, ranged from 7.5 percent to
19.6 percent, while the production of chemical products and
building materials was also accelerated a bit, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The sales for washing machines, freezers and household
air-conditioners increased by 20 percent in August. The
information products, such as program-controlled switching gear,
computers, PCs and integrated circuits, are on high market demand,
and generated an increase of more than 24 percent in production.
</P>
<P>
The SSB report said that a hopeful revival is now dawning on
China's industrial sector, which made profits of 73.7 billion yuan
in the first seven months of this year, up 33 percent on an annual
basis. The profits of state-owned enterprises reached 14.73
billion yuan, up 92.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the report noted that the losses of industrial
enterprises is still a thorny nut far from being thoroughly
solved.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
