<HEADLINE> China's First Institute of Building Automation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China's first institute
specializing in research and teaching of automation technologies
related to the building industry was established in Tianjin today.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin University-Honeywell Building Automation
Institute deals with computer networks and computer controls,
automation technologies, and sensor and instrument technologies.
</P>
<P>
The institute was founded by Tianjin University and the
Honeywell Corporation. Its will train teachers, postgraduates and
senior students of Tianjin University, and employees and customers
of the Honeywell Corporation.
</P>
<P>
Building automation is a new area of study in management
systems that monitor and control modern building security systems,
fire fighting, water and power supplies, air-conditioning and
communication.
</P>
<P>
Yueguo Tsai, director of the Honeywell Corporation (China
Region), said that the company hopes to contribute to China's
building automation development and do more business by
co-operating with China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
