<HEADLINE> Albanian PM Starts West Europe Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos
Nano Began a West Europe trip today to seek economic aid and entry
into the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Nano's press
office announced.
</P>
<P>
The visit, the first since Nano took office in July, will take
him to Austria, Luxembourg and Belgium, the office said.
</P>
<P>
Nano will seek economic aid from the European Union (EU) and
try to strengthen ties between Albania and West European countries.
</P>
<P>
Nano is scheduled to meet EU President Jacques Santer, EU
Commissioner for Foreign Relations Hans van den Broek, Austrian
Federal Chancellor Viktor Klima and Luxembourg Prime Minister
Jean-Claude Juncker during his four-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The visit is prior to two meetings involving economic aid to
Albania -- a meeting of EU Commission for Foreign Relations in
Rome early in October and an International Monetary Fund (IMF)
meeting in Brussels at the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
On September 3, an IMF delegation reached an agreement in
principle with the Albanian government on emergency aid to the
Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
However, the agreement needs to be approved at the Brussels
meeting.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Nano will meet NATO Secretary-general Javier
Solana and brief NATO on the domestic and foreign policies of
Albania and the country's plan for joining the Western military
alliance.
</P>
<P>
Nano will express the desire for further developing relations
with NATO and Albania agrees to give NATO a role in overseeing the
modernization of its army, said the office. 
</P>
</TEXT>
