<HEADLINE> Manila to Host ASEAN Shippers Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Some 75 delegates from 15
countries and regions will gather in Manila to attend the 20th
Annual Meeting of the Federation of ASEAN Shippers' Council (FASC)
on October 1-3.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Reyes, director of the Philippine Shippers' Bureau of
the Department of Trade and Industry, said the conference will
discuss the recent world trade development, industry concerns and
various matters affecting the FASC members and international
community.
</P>
<P>
Hosting of annual meetings of FASC is rotated among member
countries. Last year's 19th annual meeting was held in Bangkok,
Thailand, according to the Philippine News Agency report today.
</P>
<P>
Countries and international shipping councils to be represented
during the three-day meeting include the FASC Executive Committee
members consisting of the National Shippers' Councils of
Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore, Thailand and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Associate members including the Australia Peak Shippers
Association, Hong Kong Shippers' Council, Korean Shippers'
Council, Council of Bangladesh and Sri Lanka Shippers' Council
will likewise be represented, the report quoted Reyes as saying.
</P>
<P>
Observers from Japan, Macao, China and the European Union are
also expected to take part in the activity.  
</P>
