<HEADLINE> North China Port City Builds Polyester Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The second-phase construction of a
large polyester project commenced recently in the north
China port city of Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The project will be built at a total cost of 9.13 billion yuan
provided by the Tianjin Petrochemical Company. The new facility
will have a yearly production capacity of 200,000 tons when put
into operation in October 2000.
</P>
<P>
First phase construction of the project started in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Petrochemical Company, established in the 1970s and
one of China's four major chemical fiber producers, now has an
annual polyester production capacity of 10,000 tons. 
</P>
