<HEADLINE> Thailand Adjusts 8th National Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government today
completed the adjustment of its Eighth National Economic and
Social Development Plan, playing down the country's economic
growth target during 1997-2001.
</P>
<P>
Under the revised plan, the average economic growth target
during the five years is lowered to 4.9 percent from 8 percent set
previously.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's average inflation rate target is relaxed
to 5.6 percent from 4.5 percent during the five years and the
average current account deficit target is revised to 3.6 percent
of the gross national product (GDP) instead of 3.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Thai Cabinet approved the adjustment at its regular meeting
today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
