<HEADLINE> Becker to Play in Grand Slam Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker was reportedly to
accept a wild card to play in the Grand Slam Cup in Munich
starting on September 23.
</P>
<P>
The Gram Slam Cup, the most lucrative tournament in tennis
which was created by his former manager and friend Axel
Meyer-Woelden, was believed to be Becker's last appearance at a
major tournament.
</P>
<P>
Last year Becker won the event which brings together the top
performers from the four grand slams -- Wimbledon and the U.S.,
French and Australian Opens.
</P>
<P>
The Grand Slam Cup, which pays out an astonishing 1.5 million
U.S. dollars to the winner plus appearance bonuses to grand slam
champions, was created at the start of the 1990s by Meyer-Woelden
who died recently.
</P>
<P>
Among Becker's opponents will be world number one Pete Sampras,
who won the Australian Open and Wimbledon, as well as U.S. Open
champion Patrick Rafter of Australia and French Open winner
Gustavo Kuerten of Brazil. 
</P>
