<HEADLINE> EU Calls for Decentralized Rural Development Plans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUXEMBOURG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s
rural development policy should be as decentralized as possible so
member countries can find solutions to meet their individual
needs, an EU official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Franz Fischler, the EU commissioner responsible for agriculture
and rural development, made the remark at a three-day informal
meeting of EU agriculture ministers held in Echternach,
Luxembourg, which closed Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"In view of the great diversity of rural areas in the Union, it
is natural that a policy for their development must be based on
the principle of subsidiarity," the commissioner said.
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, the EU's executive body, has
reportedly proposed a reform of the whole gamut of its rural
development policy, which is being criticized for being too
complicated and inconsistent.
</P>
<P>
The EU is planning to let all its member states and regions
define their own rural development strategies in the future,
Fischler told the meeting Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
