<HEADLINE> Maldives to Get ADB Loan for Power Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) said today it has approved a 7 million U.S. dollar
concessional loan for a power development project in Maldives.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, the Manila-based multilateral financial
body said the loan will be used to increase generating capacity of
Maldives' State Electric Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The project will significantly increase the country's power
supply, and is expected to ease a power shortage in the capital
city of Male, the ADB said.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which will come from the bank's Special Fund
resources, is interest-free and carries a service charge of 1
percent per annum. 
</P>
