<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loan to Laos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) today approved a 46 million U.S. dollar concessional loan
for a road project in Laos.
</P>
<P>
The road project will improve about 300 kilometers of two
national road sections and about 100 kilometers of feeder roads in
Xieng Khouang province, the Manila-based ADB said in a news
release.
</P>
<P>
The project will promote the economic development of Xieng
Khouang province which, although has abundant natural resources,
is isolated for about eight months each year because of poor
roads.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan is from the bank's Special Funds, which means it
is interest-free, carries a service charge of 1 percent per annum
and is repayable over 40 years, including a 10-year grace period.
