<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Reaction to Panama's Inviting Taiwan to Canal Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- China has expressed regret
over Panama's decision to invite Taiwan authorities to Universal
Congress on the Panama Canal.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian government has disregarded China's solemn
statements and admonitions, and has acted in violation of the UN
Charter and the UN resolution No. 2758, a Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman said in response to a question about the matter at a
press conference today.
</P>
<P>
It has in fact provided an opportunity for Taiwan authorities
to continue their attempts to split the motherland, and has
jeopardized China's sovereignty and interference in China's
domestic affairs, Shen Guofang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that this decision by the Panamanian government has
had a negative effect, and that the leaders of the United Nations
and its relevant organs as well as leaders of most countries did
not participate in the conference.
</P>
<P>
China is one of the countries that strongly supports the just
struggle of the Panamanian people to resume sovereignty over the
Panama Canal, and that it supports the two resolutions adopted by
the UN on the world conferences on the issue, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government reiterates its readiness to develop
relations with all countries based on the Five Principles of
Peaceful Co-existence, he said, expressing the hope that Panama
will take concrete actions to respond positively to China's
efforts in the normalization of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Shen went on to say that the leaders of the Taiwan authorities,
while saying that they are willing to improve relations across the
straits, continue their attempts to create "Two Chinas", or "One
China, One Taiwan".
</P>
<P>
These actions undermine the improvement of cross-straits
relations and the peaceful reunification process, the spokesman
said, expressing the hope that the Taiwan authorities will take
effective measures to halt such activities to split the
motherland.  
</P>
