<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 12:45 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE>   Aid Coordination Committee Concerns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Local Aid Coordination
Committee For Palestine expressed here today its grave concern
over the Israeli closure on the Palestinian territories and
asked donor nations to speed up their aids to the Palestinian
people.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting here, representatives from the United Nations
Office of the Coordinator in the Occupied Territories, World
Bank's Resident Mission in the West Bank and Gaza, the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) and the donor nations also expressed
their condemnation of the terrorist attacks in Jerusalem on July
30 and September 4.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli delegation was not present at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
While security issues concern all, the impact of closure and
withholding of revenue transfer (by Israel) are considered
counterproductive to security concerns. It undermines the key
cornerstone on which the donor community participate in the peace
process, the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
Donors are answerable to internal budgetary processes which
will question the continuing commitment of resources to a
development process damaged by closures, it said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting said that Israeli government's withholding of
revenue transfer due to the PNA was not related to security.
</P>
<P>
Transfers are the basis for establishing financially sustainable
Palestinian institutions for self-governance. Without a stable
income and trade, the PNA can not provide for the welfare of its
people and to establish a sound economic and social platform for
Palestinian development is clearly in the interests of the entire
region, it said.
</P>
<P>
PNA representative told the meeting that almost 100 million
U.S. dollars in revenue transfer is now being withheld by Israel
and appealed to donors to provide 50 million U.S. dollars in
bridging finance.
</P>
<P>
The meeting urged the donor nations to provide more financial
aid to PNA.
</P>
<P>
Israel imposed total closures on Palestinian territories on
Thursday following the bombing blasts in Jerusalem. The previous
closure was imposed on July 30 for the same reason. 
</P>
</TEXT>
