<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda Coffee Export Down by 6.1 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's overall coffee
export earnings decreased by 6.1 percent, from 358.3 million U.S.
Dollars in 1995/1996 to 336.6 million in 1996/1997 due to low
world prices, Uganda Coffee Development Authority said.
</P>
<P>
In the past eleven months of 1996/1997 coffee season, the
total coffee export topped 4 million bags (60 kilos per bag),
witnessing a 6.36 percent increase from 3.7 million bags recorded
in the same period in 1995/1996 season, it said in a report
available today.
</P>
<P>
The decline of coffee export earnings of the country was
blamed on the estimated increased coffee yield of Brazil, the
main coffee exporter in the world.
</P>
<P>
The other reason causing the decline of the coffee export of
the country is the increased stocks in the United States, the
main consumer of coffee and the increased estimated coffee yield
of Colombia from 10.2 million bags to 10.6 million bags.
</P>
<P>
But the news of impact on coffee production caused by El Nino
improved to some extent the buying condition in the world market,
the report noted.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is a traditional cash crop in Uganda which is one of
the leading coffee exporters in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
