<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Re-exports Jump 12 Percent in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's
re-exports in June jumped by 12 percent over last year while
domestic exports increased by 3.4 percent, local press reports
said today.
</P>
<P>
Taken together, total exports rose by 11 percent. Concurrently
the volume of imports gained 8.6 percent, according to the Census
and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The volume of Hong Kong's re-exports in the first half of this
year went up by 6.5 percent compared with the same period of last
year while its volume of domestic exports decreased by 1.9
percent. Put together, the volume of total exports climbed by 5.1
percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, its imports soared by 6.7 percent from January to
June this year.
</P>
<P>
The growth in the volume of trade derived from an increase in
trade value with the effect of price changes discounted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
