<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Joblessness Rises in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The number of jobless people in
Germany climbed by 49,000 to a seasonally adjusted 4.456 million
in August, the Nuremberg-based Federal Labour Office reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The adjusted unemployment rate rose slightly from 11.5 percent
to 11.6 percent, while the non-adjusted unemployment rate remained
unchanged at 11.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The figure last month was 470,400 higher compared with the same
month last year, the office said.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment has been most severe in west Germany, with 3.044
million of the total 4.456 million being in the region.
</P>
<P>
The German Trade Unions Federation DGB said the figures
represent a sad post-war record for the month of August. It said a
three percent medium-term growth of economy was necessary to
reverse the trend in the job market.
</P>
<P>
Labour Office President Bernhard Jagoda said September would be
the key month to see if a turnabout would occur in the job market.
</P>
<P>
Normally, joblessness drops sharply in September, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
