<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Attack Foreign ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Tamil Rebels attacked a
Panama-registered vessel this morning at seas near Pulmoddai in
Northern province of Sri Lanka, naval sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the vessel, which was carrying materials
towards the Pulmoddai Mineral Sands Corporation, was being
escorted by the Sri Lankan Army when it was attacked.
</P>
<P>
Two soldiers are reported to have been killed in the attack
while seven army persons and eight of the crew members were
missing following the attack.
</P>
<P>
The navy in a search operation sighted eight Tamil rebel boats
in the vicinity and had destroyed them all, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
The liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels have been
fighting a war for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of
the country since 1983.
</P>
<P>
On July 8, the LTTE hijacked a vessel of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea which was hired by the Sri Lankan
government to transport goods to the Jaffna Peninsula in the north
when it was on way to Colombo from the north.  
</P>
