<HEADLINE> Turkish Prime Minister Leaves for Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Prime Minister Mesut
Yilmaz left here today for Kazakhstan on a three-day official
visit to the central Asian country.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference at the airport before his
departure, Yilmaz said that his visit to Kazakhstan is mainly
aimed at furthering the friendly relations between the two
nations.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz, accompanied by a large group of Turkish businessmen,
said that he would explore ways to expand Turkey's economic
cooperation with Kazakhstan in all fields.
</P>
<P>
An earlier written statement issued by the Turkish Prime
Ministry Press Office said that Yilmaz will hold talks with
Kazakh leaders on regional and international issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
Yilmaz is scheduled to meet Kazakh President Nursultan
Nazarbayev and Prime Minister Akezhan Kazhegeldin during his stay
in Alma-Ata, the capital of Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources here noted Yilmaz's tour to Kazakhstan, the
firs visit abroad since he took office in June, shows in itself
that Turkey attaches special importance to the region.
</P>
<P>
A planned trip to Turkmenistan following his visit to
Kazakhstan has been canceled for Turkmen President Saparmurad
Niyazov's health reason, according to the Turkish Foreign
Ministry. 
</P>
