<HEADLINE> Singapore PM to Visit Mexico, United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong will make an official visit to Mexico and travel to the
United States from Wednesday through next Thursday, the Prime
Minister's Office announced today.
</P>
<P>
It said Goh will be making an official visit to Mexico from
Wednesday to Sunday and it will be the first visit ever by a
Singapore Prime Minister to Mexico.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Mexico City, Goh will have a private as well
as a delegation meeting with Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo
Ponce de Leon. He will also address a business luncheon organized
by the Mexican Businessmen's Council for International Affairs,
the Prime Minister's Office said.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister is to be accompanied by Lim Hng Kiang,
Minister for National Development and Second Minister for Foreign
Affairs, a delegation of senior government officials, and a
45-member business delegation, it said.
</P>
<P>
After Mexico, Goh will stopover at Los Angeles where he will
visit Universal Studios and Hughes Electronics. Then he will
proceed to Chicago where he will deliver a keynote address to the
US-ASEAN (Association of South East Asian Nations) Business
Council to mark the 30th anniversary of the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
In Chicago, the Prime Minister will also meet the US Secretary
of Commerce William Daley, the Governor of Illinois Jim Edgar, and
the Mayor of Chicago Richard Daley, it said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
