<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Meets Romanian Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and
Foreign Minister Qian Qichen met here today with Adrian Severin,
Romanian minister of state and minister of foreign affairs, who is
accompanying Romanian President Contantinescu on a visit to China.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers agreed that Chinese President Jiang
Zemin's visit to Romania last year and the current China tour by
President Contantinescu have been of major significance for
enhancing mutual understanding and expanding bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They also briefed each other on the situation in their
respective regions and the foreign policies of their respective
countries.
</P>
<P>
Severin said that Romania favors a multipolar world in which
Europe and Asia can engage in mutually beneficial
collaboration. He said that Romania and China should work jointly
to achieve the objective.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China appreciates the Romanian practice of
enhancing its ties with countries in other regions, while adhering
to the policy of maintaining good relations with neighboring
countries. He said that China hopes Romania will play a bigger
role in safeguarding the peace and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Romania is China's major cooperative partner in central and
east Europe, and the two countries have cooperated closely and
supported each other in international organizations, said Qian,
adding that the foreign ministries of the two nations have
maintained a highly beneficial cooperative relationship.
</P>
<P>
China is fully prepared to continue and strengthen
consultations and cooperation with Romania in the realm of
international affairs, said Qian. 
</P>
</TEXT>
