<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chen Xitong Expelled From Party </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chen Xitong, former secretary
of the Beijing Municipal Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), was expelled from the Party for corruption, according to a
decision announced by the Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection of the CPC here today.
</P>
<P>
The decision to expel Chen was made by the Central Commission
for Discipline Inspection on August 29.
</P>
<P>
Since Chen had offended China's Criminal Law in certain
aspects, the CPC Central Commission for Discipline Inspection also
suggested that the country's judicial organs step in and handle
the case in accordance with the law.
</P>
<P>
The procuratorial organs have already started legal proceedings
against Chen, who was also former member of the Political Bureau
of the CPC's Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision of the Fifth Plenum of the 14th CPC
Central Committee, the CPC Central Commission for Discipline
Inspection, along with other relevant departments, had earlier
made further investigation into Chen's corruption case.
</P>
<P>
It has since been established that Chen, taking advantage of
his position, had accepted and embezzled a large number of
valuable items; and had squandered a large amount of public fund
to support a corrupt and decadent life.
</P>
<P>
He had also abused his power to help his relatives and aides to
run businesses and seek illicit interests, and seriously neglected
his duty, being responsible to a grave extent for the law-breaking
and criminal activities of Wang Baosen, a former vice-mayor of
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The Central Commission for Discipline Inspection held that Chen
had seriously violated the Party's discipline and caused extremely
severe damage to the prestige of the Party and state, thus
completely discrediting himself as a communist.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the Constitution of the CPC and relevant
stipulations in the Penalty Regulations of the CPC (on a trial
basis), and with the approval of the Party Central Committee, the
Commission decided to expel Chen from the Party.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
