<HEADLINE> Thousands Migrate From Key Power Station Area (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The local government provided a subsidy of over 200 yuan for
per square meter construction of new brick and wood homes for
local farmers.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the government provided interest-free loans or
building materials and resettlement allowances for
poverty-stricken families unable to afford new homes.
</P>
<P>
Officials pointed out that the principle for the resettlement
efforts have centered on "the retention of wealth."
</P>
<P>
The city has resettled nearly 20,000 migrants in 40
resettlement areas which have completed the construction of
infrastructure facilities such as water and power generation
systems and highways.
</P>
<P>
Some 350,000 sq.m. of housing have been constructed for
migrants, with the per capita living space standing at 19 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
Yanbian County has already completed over 60 percent of its
resettlement effort. Some 480,000 sq.m. of floor space are
currently under construction, with the 260,000 sq.m. of housing
already completed including residential quarters covering 230,000
square meters.
</P>
<P>
The construction of other projects, including roads, a posts
and telecommunications system and broadcasting and television
facilities is being accelerated during the ongoing resettlement
program.
</P>
<P>
According to the original plan, the migrant work at Ertan
Hydropower Station began in 1995 and will last for three years.
</P>
