<HEADLINE> Uganda Develops Local Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Uganda Tourism Board (UTB) is
to inaugurate its tourism items including bird watching, nature
walking and sport fishing this year in Lodon Warld Travel Market
(WTM), ''The New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
Uganda serves these items now, but it will spread some of them
to more scenic spots, and the activities to inaugurate the
services internationally will start in November at the world
tourism market in London, UTB Sales and Marketing Executive
Ignatius Nakishero said.
</P>
<P>
Tourism theme of Mountain Gorilla initiated by Uganda in the
WTM led to a 18 percent increase last year in the tourists
visiting the country, Nakishero said.
</P>
<P>
Uganda serves bird watching in Queen Elizabeth Game Park in
the west and it will spread soon to Bwindi Forest Reseve and Lake
Mburo and Murchison Falls game Park in the same area. Sport
fishing is afforded in Murchison Falls in the west, while ADN
nature walks is done in Bwindi Forest, Kibale and Queen Elizabeth
Game Park in the west.
</P>
<P>
Forteen Uganda companies will take part in WTM later this
year, the paper said. 
</P>
