<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Romanian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of
China's National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met
today with visiting Romanian President Emil Constantinescu.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders pledged to promote Sino-Romanian relations
through friendly contacts and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that his important talks Monday with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin laid a solid foundation for
furthering the cooperative bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
China and Romania have reinforced their cooperation in every
field in recent years, Qiao said. The President's ongoing China
tour fully indicates that both sides attach importance to
advancing bilateral relations, he added.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said he has witnessed the great progress of
China's economy in recent years. He noted that the Chinese people
are wise, industrious and united. This provides an important
guarantee for the nation's sustained development, the President
said. He also said that China's ways of development merit
reference for other countries.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that contacts between parliaments of the two
countries constitute an important aspect of Sino-Romanian ties. He
said China appreciates the establishment of Romania-China
Friendship Group which consists of representatives of
different parties in the Romanian congress.
</P>
<P>
Qiao stated that NPC treasures its friendly ties with the
Romanian congress and is fully ready to strengthen contacts
between the two parliaments.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian President said he fully supports the operations of
the Romania-China Friendship Group.
</P>
<P>
Bao Xuding, chairman of the Chinese Government Reception
Committee and Minister of Machinery Industry, and Adrian Severin,
Romanian Minister of State and Minister of Foreign Affairs, were
present at the meeting. 
