<HEADLINE> Northeastern Chinese City's Rural Projects For Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, a large industrial
city and major farm production base in Liaoning province in
northeastern China, has economic development plans for rural areas
that call for the use of foreign investment.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors from the United States, Japan, the Republic
of Korea and Thailand recently attended an investment meeting held
by the city government, which offered about 100 projects for
investment. These projects covered the fields of resource
development, farm products, hi-tech agricultural development,
breeding, village-based tourism, and enterprise property.
</P>
<P>
The Liaoning Province has 610,000 ha. of cultivated land,
27,000 ha. of arable land, 27,000 ha. of hilly land that could be
afforested, and 27,000 ha. of water that could be used for aquatic
products.
</P>
<P>
According to Vice-mayor Jin Mingshi, the Shenyang City has 10
major rural production bases for grain, vegetables, eggs, pigs,
fruits, seeds, aquatic products, and flowers.
</P>
<P>
Villages have nearly 1,000 foreign-funded firms and the
Zhangshi Farm Products Wholesale Market, which is being built at a
cost of 80 million US dollars, is one of the largest projects
built with foreign funds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
