<HEADLINE> S. Africa Makes Huge Profit By Selling Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A senior South African
official confirmed that South Africa sold weapons and military
technology worth 125 million U.S. dollars in the first six months of
this year.
</P>
<P>
Part of this year's exports included the 10.6-million U.S. Dollar
sale of non-lethal hardware to Rwanda to help restore law and order
there, local daily the Citizen today quoted National Conventional Arms
Control Committee Chairman Kadier Asmal as reporting.
</P>
<P>
Big arms deals with some countries were still in the pipeline,
Asmal said, noting European countries were particularly interested in
the advances the South African arms industry had made in the
electronics field. but he did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Sources, who declined to be named, said that arms deals with
Kuwait and Saudi Arabia worth over two billion U.S.Dollars were
under negotiation.
</P>
<P>
South Africa faced international outrage when it tried to sell
650 million U.S.Dollars of sophisticated guidance systems to Syria
for its russia-made tanks earlier this year. 
</P>
