<HEADLINE> Chinese And Hungarian Military Heads Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Fu Quanyou, Chief of General
Staff of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA), said here
today that the visit by Hungarian army leader is conducive to
promoting friendly contacts between the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Fu made the remarks during his talks with Vegh Ferenc,
Commander and Chief of General Staff of the National Army of
Hungary. The visit would also be beneficial to the overall
development of relations between the two countries, Fu added.
</P>
<P>
