safeguarding national sovereignty, and developing national
economies and this is a solid foundation for Sino-Hungarian
friendly ties," he said.
</P>
<P>
The PLA places great importance on friendly ties with the
Hungarian army and is ready to have exchanges and co-operation in
various fields in the spirit of mutual respect, equality and
mutual benefit, and seeking common grounds while preserving
differences, Fu said.
</P>
<P>
Vegh said that China is a strategic force for safeguarding
world peace and stability and that China's foreign policy is
peaceful in nature. He said he hopes to reinforce friendly
exchanges between the two nations, and between the two armies in
particular.
</P>
<P>
Present at the talks was Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the
PLA general staff.
</P>
<P>
