<HEADLINE> Four Armed Smugglers Killed in Northeast Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Four armed smugglers were
killed in clashes with Iranian armed policemen in northeast Iran
in the past two days, the official news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that the clashes broke out in Khorasan province's
Torbat-Jaam and Qa'en towns, about 900 kilometers east of Iran's
capital of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The provincial law enforcement department indicated that a
unspecified number of smugglers were injured in the fightings in
the mountainous areas. Some 550 kilograms of drugs and some
weapons were seized from the smugglers, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the law enforcement forces in separate operations
arrested eight drug traffickers and seized 262 kilograms of
narcotic drugs in the provincial capital city of Mashhad and the
town of Chenaran.
</P>
<P>
Iran seized 175 tons of narcotics and arrested 12,000 drug
traffickers during the last Iranian calendar year ending March
20, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Iran is used by smugglers as a transit for drugs coming from
Pakistan and Afghanistan destined for Europe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
