<HEADLINE> President's Visit Promote Sino-Romanian Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said
today that the current visit by Romanian President Emil
Constantinescu will elevate Sino-Romanian relations to a new level.
</P>
<P>
Li met with Constantinescu today and noted that the Chinese
government attaches great importance to relations with Romania.
</P>
<P>
He added that China respects the independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity of Romania, the choice of the Romanian
people on their development path, and the domestic and foreign
policies of the Romanian government formulated according to the
country's national conditions.
</P>
<P>
Li told Constantinescu that China is willing to join Romania in
an effort to further their friendly relations and cooperation on
the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said the purpose of his visit is to enhance
direct dialogue and contacts between the leaders of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said the friendly relations between the two countries are
strong and beyond ideological differences. Constantinescu added
that any term of the Romanian government will continue to
strengthen relations.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian President said his country needs to exchange views
with China when forming its overall foreign policy strategy, and
stressed that his current visit is important for not only
enhancing bilateral relations, but also for strengthening
cooperation in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China is willing to expand economic ties with
Romania in line with the principle of equality and mutual
benefit. He said he hopes Romanian products would be more
competitive on the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Major Romanian and Chinese companies should expand contacts and
gain a better awareness of economic changes and the trade
environments in the two countries, said Li, adding that both
governments should encourage multiple forms of direct cooperation
between enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu said that Romania and China should strengthen
their relationship based on mutual trust and extend greater
efforts to promote economic and trade ties.
</P>
<P>
Both Li and Constantinescu expressed confidence in the further
development of economic and trade relations between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li briefed Constantinescu on China's economic development and
China's efforts in deepening reform and opening wider to the
outside world. He said China and Romania can learn from each other
in this regard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
