<HEADLINE> Deng's Theory to Guide China Into 21st Century (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, September 9 (Xinhua) -- "The forthcoming 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) will undoubtedly
uphold the banner of Deng Xiaoping's theory on building socialism
with Chinese characteristics and propel China's socialist cause
towards the 21st century," according to Wan Guoquan, vice-chairman
of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC).
</P>
<P>
"Simply stated, we will continue economic restructuring and
pursue accelerated development," said Wan in an excited expression
of confidence concerning the forthcoming 15th CPC National
Congress scheduled to open on September 12th.
</P>
<P>
China's achievements in reform and opening over the past few
decades serve as a strong testament to the rationality and
feasibility of the theory, said Wan.
</P>
<P>
One month ago, Wan, who also serves as vice-chairman of the
Central Committee of the China Democratic National Construction
Association (CDNCA), attended a special symposium the CPC Central
Committee held to solicit opinions on a draft of the work report
to be presented during the 15th CPC congress. Representatives from
all eight non-communist parties in China and non-party personages
attended the symposium.
</P>
<P>
According to Wan, "As normal, General Secretary Jiang Zemin of
the CPC Central Committee focused his total attention on matters
at hand. The event featured a series of heart-to-heart
discussions, and we reserved little in frank exchanges of
opinions."
</P>
<P>
The multiparty cooperation and political consultation system
under the leadership of the CPC is the basic political system in
China. "I've joined in many effective and productive
consultations," said Wan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0227 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng's Theory to Guide China into 21st Century (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wan noted that the system's major advantage lies in its
potential to unite as many people as possible to advance the
nation's socialist cause.
</P>
<P>
"Speaking from personal experience, I believe the system will
remain magically effective in promoting the country's continued
economic development," said Wan, who has maintained close contacts
with three generations of CPC leadership over the past half
century, In addition, Wan's democratic party has consistently
maintained friendly cooperative relationship with the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Wan's father was a famous Kuomintang general during the War of
Resistance Against Japan. Wan himself joined the CDNCA in 1950 and
was appointed as its vice-chairman in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Wan responded to a question concerning why major policies
seldom arouse dissident opinions when published by pointing to the
fact that all policies are subject to heated discussions and
careful revisions prior to publication.
</P>
<P>
According to Wan, "Chinese democracy is in no way empty."
</P>
<P>
Wan, who also serves as president of the China Council for the
Promotion of Peaceful Reunification, called for political
negotiations between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits in order
to pave way for the reunification of the motherland in the new
century.
</P>
<P>
Wan was quoted as saying that the "One Country, Two Systems"
principle, which proved practical in China's successful resumption
of sovereignty over Hong Kong, is fully applicable to the issue of
Taiwan. 
</P>
