<HEADLINE> Electronics Promote Growth of ICBC Shanghai Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Branch of the
Industrial and Commercial Bank of China (ICBC) has exerted great
efforts over the past decade to introduce the latest electronic
equipment.
</P>
<P>
The efforts have paid off and the branch has grown into the
largest banking operation in Shanghai, the country's largest
industrial city and a major financial center.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai branch leads domestic competitors in the ongoing
nationwide campaign to introduce state-of-the-art electronics and
is an industry leader in terms of computerization, the issuance of
credit cards, networking and number of operational ATMs.
</P>
<P>
The branch has networked 100 percent of its banking operations
over the past 10 years, in addition to opening synchronous
electronic clearances for institutional clients, reducing the time
required for related transactions from 24 hours to only one hour.
</P>
<P>
Its 450 ATMs are linked to the international VISA/PLUS network
and its Peony Lingtong Cards can be used in ICBC branches in 16
cities.
</P>
<P>
Director Mao Yingliang notes that the ICBC Shanghai Branch has
entered a new electronics era ahead of other competitors, and has
thus laid a solid foundation for transforming the city into an
international financial hub.  
</P>
