<HEADLINE> Book Series on Mongolian Studies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Nine books on Mongolian studies
were recently published, including works related to Mongolian fine
arts, music, grottos, medicine, and philosophy of Genghis Khan.
</P>
<P>
The books, written in both Chinese and Mongolian languages,
are the first group in a 60-volume series scheduled for
publication over the next five years.
</P>
<P>
Mongolian studies were introduced in the 1950's and have since
attracted scholars from over 50 countries and regions, including
more than 2,000 Chinese scholars.
</P>
<P>
China is currently in the process of establishing a national
society for Mongolian studies. 
