<HEADLINE> Sino-French Garment College in Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, September 9 (Xinhua)-- The International Garment
College attached to Dalian University, Liaoning Province, has
enrolled its first class of 40 students.
</P>
<P>
The college is jointly funded by Dalian University, the Dalian
Radio and TV Administration, Dayang Group and a French fashion
association.
</P>
<P>
Dalian University has provided the new college with classrooms,
teaching equipment and some teachers, with the French association
responsible for teaching guidelines, training tutors and hiring
fashion designers and teachers.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, which hopes to become a "Fashion City", has hosted an
annual international fashion fair since 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
