<HEADLINE> China to Hold Confucius Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 9 (Xinhua) -- People living in Qufu, the home
of Confucius, will host a festival later this month to honor the
2,548th birth anniversary of the great master.
</P>
<P>
The festive activities, to be held between September 26 and
October 10, will include theatrical performances, seminars and
exhibitions in and around Qufu in east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
Confucius, one of the most famous philosophers in ancient
China, spread his doctrines to both political figures and ordinary
citizens, calling on them to love each other and adhere to secular
rules. Confucianism remains popular in many Asian countries and
regions even today.
</P>
<P>
During China's chaotic Culture Revolution (1966-76), Confucius
was criticized as the promoter of decadent culture.
</P>
<P>
Many descendents of Confucius, including a number who live
overseas, will return to Qufu to pay homage to the master during
the festival which is part of a national tourism program.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
