<HEADLINE> Qinghai Water Control Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, September 9 (Xinhua) -- The Heiquan Reservoir, the
largest water control project of northwest China's Qinghai
Province, has successfully blocked the Beichuan River, a tributary
of the Huangshui River.
</P>
<P>
The reservoir is located in the upper reaches of Beichuan River
in the Hui-Tu Autonomous County, Datong, Qinghai Province. The
multifunctional water control project will improve irrigation, the
urban water supply, flood control, power generation and
environmental protection in the county.
</P>
<P>
The project will require the construction of a reservoir dam
some 123.5 meters in height, spillways, water diversion tunnels
and tunnels for irrigation and power generation, as well as three
generator rooms and urban water supply facilities.
</P>
<P>
The water control project was approved by the State Council in
December of 1995. Construction commenced in September 1996 and the
project will be completed in four and a half years at a cost of
526 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Project Director Ma Yuanbiao said completion of the reservoir
will improve the use ratio of water resources in the Huangshui
River Valley, expand irrigation coverage and provide Xining, the
capital of Qinghai, with 135 million tons of water annually for
industrial and private use.  
</P>
</TEXT>
