<HEADLINE> Tamil Rebel Arrested for Killing Ruling Party Organizer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have
arrested a Tamil rebel in connection with the 1995 murder of
ruling party organizer Kumaraswamy Vinodhan, the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The rebel was one of the two men wanted by police.
</P>
<P>
"The suspect had acted as the back up man to the terrorist who
had actually pulled the trigger at Mr. Vinodhan," an investigator
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The suspect's job was to kill the organizer of the People's
Alliance should the first assassin fail in his attempt.
</P>
<P>
Police said the 28-year-old suspect's mission in Colombo before
his arrest was to reconnoiter the movements of Foreign Minister
Lakshman Kadirgamar and Deputy Defense Minister Anuruddha
Ratwatta, who are high up on the hit list of the rebels.
</P>
<P>
Police are on the lookout in Colombo for the other two suspects
who were assisting the arrested suspect.
</P>
<P>
The arrested rebel had participated in several attacks against
security forces since he joined the Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) in 1987.  
</P>
