<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0200 GMT, September 9 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- About 400 people are missing and feared drowned
after a ferry sank north of the Haitian capital before dawn on
Monday, Haiti's Radio Metropole reported.
</P>
<P>
The ferry, La Belle Gonaidienne, carrying about 700 people,
sank near the port of Montrouis, about 80 kilometers northwest of
the capital, at about 5:00 a.m. (0900 GMT). It was bringing
passengers back from the nearby island of La Gonava in the Bay of
Port-au-Prince.
</P>
<P>
Reports said as many as 300 people swam safely to shore and 25
bodies have been recovered. (Haiti-Ferry Sinking)
</P>
<P>
NICOSIA -- Cyprus will protest against Turkey's violation of
the 1936 International Treaty of Montreux on navigation in the
Bosporus Straits, a government spokesman said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Telling a daily press briefing, Manolis Christofides was
referring to last week's incident in which Turkish authorities
stopped and searched a Cyprus-flagged vessel "Diamond H", as it
arrived to transit the Bosporus.
</P>
<P>
The vessel was reportedly bound from Ukraine to Alexandria,
Egypt, carrying a cargo of steel products. (Cyprus-Turkey-Protest)
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- More than 6,000 Koreans from all walks of life
gathered here Monday to celebrate the 49th anniversary of the
founding of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
Vice presidents of DPRK Li Jong Ok and Pak Sung Chul, Vice
Premier of Administration Council Hong Song Nam and other senior
party and state officials attended the gathering.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier Hong Song Nam, who is also an alternate member of
the central committee of the Workers Party of Korea (WPK),
addressed the meeting. (DPRK-Anniversary)
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- The French government will sell 20 percent of the
stocks of the state-owned France Telecom telecommunication
monopoly, announced French Minister of Finance and Economy
Dominique Strauss-Kahn Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the government will begin the procedure of opening
20 percent of the France Telecom stocks to public and investors on
September 22 and expects its stocks to be issued in stock markets
by October 20. (France-France Telecom-Privatization)
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The joint military exercise code named Cooperative
Best Effort-97 started Monday in Adaz'i of Latvia, involving 300
soldiers from 14 NATO and non-NATO countries, Russia's Interfax
news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Taking part in the exercise are the United States, Canada,
Norway, the Netherlands, Latvia, Estonia, Finland, Poland,
Hungary,Lithuania, Moldova, Sweden, Ukraine and Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Latvian Defense Minister Talavas
Jundzis said he hopes that the exercise will help promote his
country's integration with NATO. (Baltic Sea-Exercise)
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Tung Chee Hwa, Chief Executive of China's Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), arrived here Monday for
a four-day visit to the United States.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Tung to visit the U.S. as SAR's chief
executive. He arrived here following trips to Malaysia and
Singapore. (China-Tung-US visit)
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Major U.S. airlines raised already record-high
ticket prices by 5 percent nearly across-the board, a sign of
rebust bookings for the fall and the strong economy, The Wall
Street Journal reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Business travelers will take the brunt of the increases. But
the newspaper also said many advance-purchase fares were raised
over the weekend. (US-Airlines-Prices)
</P>
<P>
STOCKHOLM -- All 12 people aboard a helicopter were feared dead
after the plane crashed Monday in the northern coastal area of
Norway.
</P>
<P>
Two bodies were recovered hours after the crash and rescuers
found some wreckage of the plane. (Norway-Plane Crash)
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The crew of Russia's Mir space station will try to
restart the main computer on board Tuesday, ground control said.
</P>
<P>
The computer failed Monday, hitting energy supplies aboard the
craft, but the crew fixed a faulty part in the computer, a
spokesman with Mission Control said. (Russia-Space-Mir) 
</P>
</TEXT>
