<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> At Least 400 Drown in Haiti Ferry Sinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 8 (Xinhua) -- About 400 people are
missing and feared drowned after a ferry sank north of the Haitian
capital before dawn on Monday, say maritime officials.
</P>
<P>
The ferry, La Belle Gonaidienne, carrying about 700 people,
sank near the port of Montrouis, about 80 kilometers northwest of
the capital, at about 5:00 a.m. (0900 GMT). It was bringing
passengers back from the nearby island of La Gonava in the Bay of
Port-au-Prince.
</P>
<P>
Reports said as many as 300 people swam safely to shore and 25
bodies have been recovered.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the accident was under investigation, and
unconfirmed reports said the ferry was overloaded.
</P>
<P>
Policemen from the nearby St. Marc police station were
assisting in the rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
The United States Coast Guard in Miami has sent a helicopter,
vessels and medical supplies to the scene of the tragedy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
