<HEADLINE> Inter to Pay Extra 1.8 Million Dollars for Ronaldo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- World soccer ruling body FIFA on
Monday ordered Italian club Inter Milan to pay Barcelona an extra
1.8 million dollars for Brazilian striker Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
FIFA appeals body rejected Inter's appeal against having to pay
further compensation to the Spanish club.
</P>
<P>
Inter has paid Barcelona 26 million dollars to buy out
Ronaldo's contract.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Brazilian, FIFA Footballer of 1996, scored 47
goals in 49 league and Cup matches for Barcelona last season.
</P>
</TEXT>
