<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Eastern Han Tomb Unearthed in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 9 (Xinhua) -- Pottery figures, silver
rings, bronzeware, ancient coins and grain have been unearthed
from a large tomb dating back to the Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220)
in Puyang city in Central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The pottery, with red designs on black paint, were shaped like
animals, stoves and other utensils, seemingly a miniature
representation of the world in which the tomb's occupants lived.
</P>
<P>
Historical records have shown that people in the Eastern Han
Dynasty paid utmost attention to burial rites.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists say that the tomb, with a passageway
leading to six burial rooms, is the one of the most complex
Eastern Han tomb ever found in the city since 1979.
</P>
<P>
Experts believed that the find will contribute to the study of
art, agriculture, burial systems and living conditions of people
living in the area some 1,700 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0269 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fossil Reserve To Trace Human Evolutionary History (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, September 9 (Xinhua) -- A huge fossil reserve dating
back 540 million years has been discovered in southwest China's
Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
and Chinese scientists say the
site will be turned into a research base for studying the earth's
early living organisms.
</P>
<P>
The fossil reserve is in Gedong village, Taijiang County, more
than 200 km from the provincial capital Guiyang. It was
discovered by researchers of the Industrial University of
Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
"The Taijiang fossil reserve contains more than 38 species and
sub-species of organisms. Most of them are worms," said Prof. Zhao
Yuanlong from the Industrial University of Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
Sixty meters above the Taijiang fossil reserve is the Kaili
fossil reserve, which was discovered in 1982, and covers more than
70 species of organisms, including Medusiform-fossils,
echinodelmas, and worms, Zhao said.
</P>
<P>
The Kaili reserve is the third-largest of its kind in the
world, only behind the two in Burgess, Canada, and Chengjiang,
in southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
About 570 million years ago, at the beginning of the Cambrian
period, most multi-cell organisms made a sudden appearance on
earth.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fossil Reserve To Trace Human Evolutionary History (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Modern day scientists are studying the fossils to determine why
the organisms' evolution got a forceful momentum at the early
period of the Cambrian period, and also why living things on earth
developed so slowly during the first five-Sixth period of the
earth's history.
</P>
<P>
The fossil reserves of Chengjiang, Taijiang, and Kaili, which
all date back to the early Cambrian period will provide valuable
data for scientists researching the early evolutionary path of
living organisms on earth.
</P>
<P>
The Wengan fossil reserve, located in the Wengan County,
Guizhou Province, is another important site with similar research
value.
</P>
<P>
From the findings at the Wengan fossil reserve, Chinese
scientists have discovered that life on earth had sexual distinctions
as early as about 600 million years ago.
</P>
<P>
The fossil reserves discovered in Guizhou, together with those
in Yunnan, constitute the a most important research base in the
world for studies on the earth's primeval living things.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, scientists from a dozen of countries,
including Britain, Canada, Germany and the United States have made
research trips to these reserves.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0271 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Export of Chinese Furniture Grows Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 9 (Xinhua) -- An increasing amount of
Chinese furniture is entering the international market.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the furniture has been exported to 25
countries and regions, earning 870 million US dollars of foreign
exchange annually.
</P>
<P>
Jia Qingwen, director of the Chinese Association of Furniture
Making, said monday during a press conference for the
International Furniture Exhibition to be held here, that Chinese
furniture has entered European and American markets in addition to
those in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
He added that the US has become China's biggest importer,
buying more than 500 million dollars worth of furniture every year.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that the Chinese furniture industry has a bright
future: it has entered a new period of development, he said, since
introducing a large number of technology and equipment from
overseas in the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The country has nearly 30,000 furniture-making factories, with
an annual output value of more than 70 billion yuan (about 8.75
billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
China has the world's largest furniture market. Authorities
estimate that the domestic demand for furniture will increase at
an annual rate of 10 percent in the next decade. In the rural
areas, the rate will reach 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The four-day international furniture exhibition, starting from
September 10, is the country's largest of the kind. More than 400
renowned manufacturers from 18 countries and regions will take
part, sources say. 
</P>
</TEXT>
