<HEADLINE> Austrian Official Hails China's Reform, Opening-up Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Heizn Fischer, president of the
National Council of Austria, said here today that the reform and
opening-up policy initiated by the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping has led the country to the right direction of development.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said that he believed the forthcoming 15th Congress of
the Communist Party of China (CPC) will reaffirm the policy and
decide to continue its implementation.
</P>
<P>
The policy is not only contributing to China's rapid economic
development but is also conducive to safeguarding world peace, he
said in an interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
Fischer has visited China several times since 1974. Leading a
Austrian parliamentary delegation, Fischer paid his latest visit
in April this year and held talks with Chinese President Jiang
Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Recalling his talks with Jiang, Fischer said that the CPC
Congress was one of the topics in their talks.
</P>
<P>
"In my personal view, it will be an important party congress
at which China's reform and opening-up policy will be reaffirmed
and continue to be implemented," he said.
</P>
<P>
"After the Congress, China will continue to march on the
charted path toward the future with full confidence," he said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that China's current policy has opened opportunities
for a positive development in the next century," he said, adding
that the people's living standards will be further improved.
</P>
<P>
He said that for a large country like China with a population
of 1.2 billion, it will inevitably face new problems and new
challenges on its way of development.
</P>
<P>
"Where there constantly emerge new challenges, there will be
vigorous and sustained development," Fischer concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
