<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Expects Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslavia is expecting a
good harvest this year, with wheat production likely to reach 9
million tons or 25 percent up on last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Per capita grain production is expected to reach 1.1 tons, the
third highest in Europe, official estimates said.
</P>
<P>
The government has adopted a series of measures in recent years
to promote agricultural production. This year alone, the federal
government provided large amounts of low-interest loans for as
many as 147 projects.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture occupies a unique position in the country's
economy, supporting 48 percent of industrial production and people
engaged in farming account for half of the total population of
10.5 million. 
</P>
