<HEADLINE> Brazil, Oman, Spain Qualify for Quarter-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Brazil, Oman and Spain joined
Germany to enter the quarter-finals today after winning their
second group matches at the Under-17 World Championship played in
Egypt.
</P>
<P>
In a Group B match played in the Suez Canal city of Ismailia,
Spain snatched a 1-0 victory today over Mali to qualify for the
quarter-finals with 6 points.
</P>
<P>
In another match played in Ismailia, Omar Gomez scored three
times to lead Mexico to a 5-0 win over New Zealand, whose rough
play resulted in five yellow cards.
</P>
<P>
The victory enabled Mexico to compete with Mali for the second
quarter-final spot in Group B, both of whom gained three points
from two matches.
</P>
<P>
In Group C, Oman today beat Austria 3-1 in a game that was
played in the pearl of the Mediterranean city of Alexandria,
winning a seat on the quarter-finals along with the powerhouse
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Five days into the championship which began Thursday, the
winless New Zealand, Austria, Costa Rica, United States and
Thailand are eliminated.
</P>
<P>
After a one-day break tomorrow, Mali and Mexico will compete
for a quarter-final berth in Group B on Wednesday, while
Argentina, Ghana and Bahrain have to fight out the best two Group
D teams. 
</P>
