<HEADLINE> Canada Post Labour Talks Break Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Talks between Canada Post and
its largest union broke down today, setting the stage for a
possible strike in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Canada Post said it had been prepared to make a new offer
today, but the union decided to pull out of the process.
</P>
<P>
"This is unacceptable behavior," Canada Post said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
The 45,000-member union said it walked away from today's talks
after seeing no signing of a good offer from the Crown
corporation.
</P>
<P>
The union now is free to apply to Canada's federal minister of
labour for a legal mandate to strike.
</P>
<P>
If taking such a step, the union would be in a strike position
by the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
The talks between Canada Post and the Union started in April.
The two sides have been unable to strike a deal due to job
security and wages differences.
</P>
<P>
Canada Post is a major postal service in Canada, delivering
about 11 billion pieces of mail every year. 
</P>
