about 200,000 cars, and will allow employment to grow to more than
2,000.
</P>
<P>
Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien, TMC President Hiroshi
Okuda and other dignitaries attended the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"This investment underlines our commitment to Canada, its
economy and the people of this community," Okuda said.
</P>
<P>
