investment, we will be very pleased," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Cambridge expansion, along with other Toyota investments
across North America, is part of Toyota's long-term commitment to
transfer manufacturing capacity to the location of sales.
</P>
<P>
By 1998, Toyota's North America production capacity will grow
to over one million vehicles from 700,000 in 1994.
</P>
<P>
When the full project is complete in 1998, Toyota's total
investment in its Cambridge operations will reach 2.2 billion
Canadian dollars (1.6 billion USD), TMC said. 
