<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- the United States on Monday
called the arrest of 35 suspected militants by the Palestinian
Authority "a positive step" on the eve of Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright's visit to the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
"We think any step in the direction of an active, relentless
effort to dismantle the security infrastructure (of the militant
groups) in the territories under the Palestinian Authority control
is a positive step in the right direction," State Department
spokesman James Foley said.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat on Monday pledged to fight
terrorism and his security forces arrested 35 suspected militants
after last week's triple suicide bombing at a Jerusalem market,
killing 7 people and injuring more than 150.
</P>
<P>
Albright will start her trip to the Middle East on Tuesday
with an attempt to revive the peace process in the region, which
has in effect gone nowhere since March when Israel decided to
build Jewish housing units in Arab East Jerusalem. 
</P>
