<HEADLINE> One Guard Killed in Prison Van Ambush </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- One prison guard was killed and
another shocked when a prison van was ambushed in Canada's second
largest city of Montreal today.
</P>
<P>
Two men ambushed the van and fired several shots through its
windshield at a railway crossing, reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The guards' vehicle was heading to pick up prisoners at a
detention centre when the ambush happened.
</P>
<P>
There were no prisoners in the vehicle at the time, police
said.
</P>
<P>
The suspects fled in a stolen van, which they later set on
fire. Two weapons were found in the burned-out hulk.
</P>
<P>
Police said the act might be the work of local biker gangs.
</P>
<P>
The attack could be an attempt to intimidate authorities who
have tried recently to crack down on the gangs, police said.
</P>
<P>
Today's attack is the second on prison guards in the past three
months. One woman guard was shot and killed in her car in June.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
