<DOCNO> XIE19970909.0309 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Smaller Stocks Outperform Bigger Ones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Blue-chip stocks on Wall
Street faded into the close of a lackluster session today, while
other measures were lifted further into record territory.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 12.77 to 7,835.18.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a 5-to-3 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 466.44 million shares,
much down from 536.40 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators posted wider gains, with advancing
issues outnumbering decliners by a sizable margin on most
exchanges.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 2.15 to 931.20, and
the NYSE composite index rose 1.14 to 485.78.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 rose 2.95 to 435.99, its ninth consecutive
record high. The Nasdaq composite index rose 9.58 to 1,645.35, and
the American Stock Exchange composite index rose 3.12 to 670.67,
both padded Friday's record highs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
